# Managed Skills Are Read-Only

Skills inside directories that contain a `.managed-skill.md` file are externally managed. **Do not modify, rename, or delete any files** in these directories.

If the user asks to change a managed skill, explain that it is managed from an external source and suggest:
- Running "update my skills" to pull the latest version
- Creating a project override rule (see below)

## Project Overrides

When applying instructions from a managed rule, check whether a corresponding `<rule-name>.overrides.mdc` file exists in the same rules directory. If it does, its instructions take precedence over any conflicting instructions in the managed rule. Non-conflicting instructions from the managed rule still apply.

Override files are project-owned and are never modified by skill updates.

Example `quality.overrides.mdc`:

    ---
    description: Project overrides for quality rule
    alwaysApply: true
    ---

    # Quality Overrides

    Type hints are optional for files under `migrations/` and `generated/`.
